org.aludratest.util.retry
Class AutoRetryImpl

java.lang.Object
  org.aludratest.util.retry.AutoRetryImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
Configurable, AutoRetry
public class AutoRetryImpl
extends Object
implements AutoRetry, Configurable

Configurable mechanism for automatically retrying a certain invocation after a certain errors for a given number of times. If each of these invocations throws an exception, the last one is returned to the caller.

Author:
Volker Bergmann

fillDefaults

public void fillDefaults(MutablePreferences preferences)
Description copied from interface: Configurable
Called by the framework to let the configurable object fill its defaults in a Preferences structure. This could be a no-op, or could even include creating complex sub-tree structures.
The framework has already filled the passed preferences object with the default values derived from ConfigProperty annotations, if any are present on the implementing class or any superclass or interface.

Specified by:
fillDefaults in interface Configurable
Parameters:
preferences - The Preferences object to fill with the defaults for the configurable object.

configure

public void configure(Preferences preferences)
Description copied from interface: Configurable
Called by the framework to let a configurable object configure itself according to the passed Preferences object. The object is allowed to store the passed Preferences reference and query it for configuration parameters when needed. It is also OK to extract all required parameters in this method.
In any case, this method should check the configuration for validness and throw an AutomationException when the configuration is invalid.

Specified by:
configure in interface Configurable
Parameters:
preferences - Configuration object for this configurable.

matches

public boolean matches(Method method,
                       Throwable t,
                       int retryCount)
Description copied from interface: AutoRetry
Checks if a retry shall be performed after an invocation of the given method caused the given Throwable. retryCount retries have already been performed for the current method invocation.

Specified by:
matches in interface AutoRetry
Parameters:
method - Method which caused the given Throwable on invocation.
t - Throwable thrown by method invocation.
retryCount - Already performed retries on the current method invocation (starts with 0).
Returns:
true if a retry of the method invocation should be performed, false otherwise.
